Temporal correlation analysis which is generally accepted as an indicator of corticocortical functional interaction, for example, increased correlation is thought to reflect increased functional connectivity between two brain sites (Bandettini et al. 1993; Friston 2011). In this study, the correlation analysis was used as an important indicator of laminar-specific functional connectivity across multiple cortical regions. Laminar-specific fMRI time courses were used and converted to the bandpass filtered time courses. The correlation is defined as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
