}{}$a,b$\end{document} indicates a voxel from one cortical region. The correlation was calculated by “corr” function in MATLAB (Type: Pearson, Rows: pairwise). Fisher-Z transform was applied prior to averaging the correlation coefficients with multiple trials (Silver and Dunlap 1987). Temporal signal-to-noise ratio (tSNR) values were calculated across the cortical depths and different cortical regions to compare differences between correlation coefficients and tSNR values (see Supplementary Fig. S3).
